<p data-index="5720">Compute net cash provided by operating activities, the net change in cash during the year, and free cash flow.</p>
<p id="BE5.13_1" data-index="5721"><span epub:type="pagebreak" role="doc-pagebreak" title="5-39" id="Page_5-39" data-index="5722"></span><b data-index="5723"><span class="codeColorBlue2" data-index="5724">BE5.13</span></b> <span class="red" data-index="5725"><b data-index="5726">(LO <a href="#h3_0003" data-index="5727" data-section-index="15" data-section-idref="h3_0003" data-target-data-index="2153">3</a>)</b></span> Ames Company reported 2020 net income of $151,000. During 2020, accounts receivable increased by $13,000 and accounts payable increased by $9,500. Depreciation expense was $44,000. Prepare the cash flows from operating activities section of the statement of cash flows.</p>
<p id="BE5.14_1" data-index="5728"><b data-index="5729"><span class="codeColorBlue2" data-index="5730">BE5.14</span></b> <span class="red" data-index="5731"><b data-index="5732">(LO <a href="#h3_0003" data-index="5733" data-section-index="15" data-section-idref="h3_0003" data-target-data-index="2153">3</a>)</b></span> Martinez Corporation engaged in the following cash transactions during 2020.</p>
<table data-index="5734">
<tbody data-index="5735">
<tr data-index="5736">
<td data-index="5737">Sale of land and building</td>
<td rowspan="7" data-index="5738">  </td>
