<p data-index="7825">Additional information:</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7826"><span class="label" data-index="7827"><b data-index="7828">1.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> <span class="x12" data-index="7829">The LIFO method of inventory value is used.</span></p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7830"><span class="label" data-index="7831"><b data-index="7832">2.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> <span class="x12" data-index="7833">The cost and fair value of the long-term investments that consist of stocks (with ownership less than 20% of total shares) are the same.</span></p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7834"><span class="label" data-index="7835"><b data-index="7836">3.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> <span class="x12" data-index="7837">The amount of the Construction in Progress account represents the costs expended to date on a building in the process of construction. (The company rents factory space at the present time.) The land on which the building is being constructed cost $85,000, as shown in the trial bal</span><span class="x12" data-index="7838">ance.</span></p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7839"><span class="label" data-index="7840"><b data-index="7841">4.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> <span class="x12" data-index="7842">The patents were purchased by the company at a cost of $40,000 and are being amortized on a straight-line basis.</span></p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7843"><span class="label" data-index="7844"><b data-index="7845">5.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> <span class="x12" data-index="7846">Of the discount on bonds payable, $2,000 will be amortized in 2021.</span></p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7847"><span class="label" data-index="7848"><b data-index="7849">6.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> <span class="x12" data-index="7850">The notes payable represent bank loans that are secured by long-term investments carried at $120,000. These bank loans are due in 2021.</span></p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7851"><span class="label" data-index="7852"><b data-index="7853">7.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> <span class="x12" data-index="7854">The bonds payable bear interest at 8% payable every December 31, and are due January 1, 2031</span><span class="x12" data-index="7855">.</span></p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="7856"><span class="label" data-index="7857"><b data-index="7858">8.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> <span class="x12" data-index="7859">600,000 shares of common stock of a par value of $1 were authorized, of which 500,000 shares were issued and outstanding.</span></p>
<h4 data-index="7860"><span class="red" data-index="7861">Instructions</span></h4>
