<h4 data-index="9193"><span class="red" data-index="9194">Instructions</span></h4>
<p class="latin1" data-index="9195"><span class="label" data-index="9196"><b data-index="9197">a.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Calculate free cash flow for Amazon for the current and prior years, and discuss its ability to finance expansion from internally generated cash. At one time, Amazon had avoided purchasing large warehouses. Instead, it used those of others. It is possible, however, that in order to increase customer <span epub:type="pagebreak" role="doc-pagebreak" title="5-57" id="Page_5-57" data-index="9198"></span>satisfaction the company could build its own warehouses. How might your impression of its ability to finance expansion change?</p>
<p class="latin1" data-index="9199"><span class="label" data-index="9200"><b data-index="9201">b.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Discuss any potential implications of the change in Amazon’s cash provided by operations from the prior year to the current year.</p>
</section>
</section>
<section id="h3_0000102" data-index="9202">
<h4 data-index="9203"><span class="codeColorBlue2" data-index="9204">Accounting, Analysis, and Principles</span></h4>
<p data-index="9205">Early in January 2021, Hopkins Company is preparing for a meeting with its bankers to discuss a loan request. Its bookkeeper provided the following accounts and balances at December 31, 2020.</p>
<table style=" border: 1px solid #000;" data-index="9206">
